message: The 'vial' tool is reusable and your most valuable asset. Always use the 'vial' on 'solid' ingredients (like dragon scale, mushroom, mandrake root, bat wing, amber) to create 'liquid, extracted' items, which are worth 30 points each. Do NOT use the vial on gas or liquid ingredients, as this results in negative value items. The 'filter' tool generally decreases item value or makes it 'poorly-filtered', so avoid it unless exploring. The highest value items (100 points) are consistently achieved by combining ONE 'magical, liquid, extracted' item with ONE 'mundane, liquid, extracted' item. Focus on this combination. Avoid combining raw gas ingredients or combining too many items, as this often leads to very low or negative values.

message: To win, create two different liquid items: one magical and one mundane. You get magical liquids by using the 'vial' on a solid magical item (e.g., dragon scale) or the 'filter' on a gas magical item (e.g., whispering wind). Similarly, get mundane liquids by using the 'vial' on a solid mundane item (e.g., obsidian) or the 'filter' on a gas mundane item (e.g., volcanic fumes). Combining one magical liquid and one mundane liquid will yield 100 points. The vial fails on gases and liquids, and the filter fails on solids and liquids, so use them correctly.
